"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150460","Department for International Trade","false","2019-10-23","<ul><li>The public appointments that the Secretary of State is responsible for making are set out in the Schedule to the Public Appointments Order in Council 2019 <a href="https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf" target="_blank">https://publicappointments.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/2019-Public-Appointments-Order-In-Council.pdf</a> as below;</li></ul><p> </p><p>Export Credits Guarantee Department (UK Export Finance)</p><p>Export Guarantee Advisory Council</p><p> </p><ul><li>Additionally, the Department for International Trade has agreed that the Trade Remedies Authority (TRA), when legally established by the Trade Bill, will be listed on the schedule to the next Public Appointments Order in Council. The Secretary of State, will then be responsible for making appointments to the TRA Board consisting of the Chair and Non-Executive Members.</li></ul>","Bournemouth West","Conor Burns",,"2019-10-23T12:48:57.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150460/answer","Biography information for Conor Burns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1150460/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-10-17","Department for International Trade: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, which public appointments she is responsible for.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","1577"
